    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-04T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="1430"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Peru/1110: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-04T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 4, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>461. Renewal rotenone price agreement<note n="49" xml:id="d1430fn49">An agreement
                        made in 1942 regarding the production and export of rotenone root and
                        powdered rotenone; not printed.</note> expiring May 10th leaves Embassy
                    option of adhering to original agreement price or voluntarily extending higher
                    price schedule as set forth in Department’s telegram 305 March 24, 3 p.m.<note
                        n="50" xml:id="d1430fn50">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Global amount of difference would approximate $100,000 to private dealers.</p>
                <p>The Embassy is disposed to use this and similar future opportunities as leverage
                    for settling; postal and other small debts considering that political
                    cooperation would not suffer thereby.</p>
                <p>Such a course to be effective would require consistent support of American
                    Government.</p>
                <p>Request instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
